  "invariant": "Pinned-divergent-digest case per AlgoVoi substrate convention. The JSON is well-formed and JCS-canonicalisable, but the SettlementReceipt.predicate.amount (1500000 micro-USDC) exceeds DelegationGrant.predicate.cap_per_tx (1000000 micro-USDC) by 50%. A protocol verifier MUST reject this receipt at the cap-respect check (spec §4.9 step CapPerTxCheck). The expected JCS hash is deterministic ; auditors and conformance harnesses pin this hash as the canonical failure case digest. Reproducing this digest from a different implementation proves cross-implementation determinism even on failure paths.",
  "notes": "Pinned-divergent-digest discipline per the AlgoVoi substrate convention (see PR #2412 for the substrate analog). The SettlementReceipt is well-formed JSON, JCS-canonicalisable to deterministic bytes, and hashes to a deterministic SHA-256. But the protocol-level cap-respect check (spec §4.9 step CapPerTxCheck) MUST reject this receipt: 1500000 > 1000000 = cap_per_tx. The receipt is included as a fixture so conformance harnesses can verify that (a) the canonicalisation discipline is deterministic on the failure path, and (b) the verifier correctly rejects when cap is exceeded. A buyer-agent caching the bounded-spend authorization context MUST refuse to forward this receipt to a settlement venue. tx_hash here is synthetic ; this receipt would never be emitted on-chain by a compliant verifier.",
